Hi thank you for reaching out. My name is Alice, I'm the FTSU here at our Trust. You can look me up on the intranet, if you need to.
As the FTSU I am here to offer you support, listen to any concerns or suggestions and understand what needs to happen.
Can you tell me some more details about your concern?
hi Alice, I am not sure I can tell you more about the concern without revealing who I am.
As your freedom to speak up guardian I am here to protect your anonymity.
Hi. Yes I get that, I think the FTSU role is great and I can see the need for you in this trust.
This is impossible. I’ve thought about this a lot. I feel very vulnerable because I am relatively new to this trust.
Patient safety is really important to me. Can I make a few suggestions that surrounds the concern I have.
I will not ask any questions surrounding your identity.
It is fine if you want to stay anonymous, I will not ask any personal questions.
I just need to know more information regarding your concern, so we can move forward.
Sure, I appreciate that this is anonymous. But I cannot really say too much.  I don’t want to be branded a whistleblower or be seen as a trouble maker.
My concern is about staffing levels. It was a near miss and I know that the trust would like us to report such events.
Under normal circumstances I’d report this.
What do you mean in normal circumstances?
You wont be seen as a whistleblower.

In the previous trust, I had the support of my management team and senior executives. I was known there. Here! No one has my back. I cannot say anymore. You are going to have to trust me that this was just a near miss.
If you implemented my suggestions, then perhaps the hospital could make some changes for better.
I recognise that staffing levels is a common concern within the NHS
My role is to support you with your concerns.
I understand. But there is a culture of bullying - well this is what my team tell me. I’ve not seen it myself. But I am worried about this.
I’ve spoken to my family and wife about my concern. They all work in care. They suggest I find a way to make a suggestion. Sorry.
I cannot give you any more information, maybe sometime in the future. But not right now.
You'll be able to read about our speaking out policies on the intranet. You can also see a letter from our CEO highlighting what he hopes and expects from us all.
Hi. Yes I’ve read these. They are great. Ok. I shall be honest. Whilst I am confident in myself. I am not confident in others that surround me if this gets out. Sorry.

My suggestion is this. Could the trust start collecting records of when requests for bank/agency staff are rejected. Give the rationale for being declined. I know finances is an issue, but I think that this would help the trust to understand if there is a
Link between incidents and rejection of requests.
Sorry I hit send too quickly there. Does this make sense?
Thank you for your suggestion, I will take this to our head of patient safety.
Is there anything else you want to mention about staffing levels?
No thanks. I think that perhaps some training needs to be provided to counter the bullying. This worked in my last trust, if not training. How about a survey and comms on bullying?
My previous trust did this, I think the results were surprisingly interesting for the leadership.
Thank you for your suggestions, is there anything else you want to raise with me?
No I don’t think so! Can I stay intouch with you via the app? Just in case I have any further thoughts on these topics?
Absolutely, I will keep this case open for the next 5 days. Of course you can always pop in to my office, if you want to.
These conversations can be done face to face but I understand how you are feeling right now.

Hi thank you for reaching out. My name is Alice and I am the FTSU here at our Trust. You can look me up on the Intranet if you need to.
As the freedom to speak up guardian I am here to offer you support, listen to any concerns or suggestions and understand what needs to happen.
Can you tell me some more information about your concern?
Hi Alice. Thanks for that. I have seen your profile and guidelines for raising concerns on the intranet. That helps a little.
Alice. Thank you for being there. I am not sure if I should report my concern. I don’t want to be seen as a whistleblower.
This week there has been a near miss that could have been avoided. I cannot give you anymore details. Sorry.
This is impossible for me, perhaps I can make a few suggestions instead of raising a concern. Because nothing can protect me.
Thank you for reaching out. As your Freedom to Speak Up Guardian I am here to protect your anonymity. You wont be seen as a whistleblower.
You're more than welcome to make any suggestions.
Yes I get that. I don’t have anyone covering my back. My team tell me that there are bullies here. I’ve not experienced it myself. And I don’t want to either.
You sound really worried. We have a zero tolerance approach to bullying and retaliation towards people who raise concerns.
That is good to hear. I think you will need to trust me that everything is ok with the near miss. It’s not ok it happened, but the team dealt with it - they are a fantastic team.  They really care.
My suggestion is that the hospital starts to record the number and rationale for declining requests for bank/agency cover.
Why do you believe this is needed?
I hope this helps. It tells you a little about what may have happened recently. I am relatively new here, but I’ve seen this approach work elsewhere.
It will help the trust understand if there is a link to staff numbers and misses and denied requests. I think there is.
If there was a report submitted monthly, then you’d be able to track and report this theme.
Thank you, this sounds like an interesting suggestion.
Can you tell me more about what has recently happened?
Feel free to give me a call, or pop into my office to see me.
Under normal circumstances I would do this. But not yet, I am still relatively new her. I am worried about speak out with my name.
Sorry new here. Ok, I’ve spoken to my wife and she works in the nhs and she suggests that I keep to the suggestions part of the concern.
I am really sorry, I want to support the Trust and CEO. But I am not ready to put my name forward. I am worried about the bullying.
I am aware of trends around bullying and staffing levels within the NHS and this is something we take really seriously. Do you have any suggestions around bullying?

I can yes, maybe we increase the level of awareness of what bullying looks and feels like. And also suggest a survey for staff.  Something anonymous maybe. It worked in Cambridge Uni. They did something like this for sexual harassment.
Thank you for your suggestion. We could use Ensos for the survey, but we will look at using all of our existing communication channels.
Sounds like a plan. It’s good to know that I can share my thoughts. As I said I’ve not seen any bullying here, but my team say it happens.
I suppose it would be good to know if it is a bigger problem that is real.  I hope not.
I am going to keep this case open for 5 days, if there is anything else you would like to tell me about. In the mean time I am going to take your suggestions forward with my executive. Thank you.
I know I said this, but you can come visit me in my office or call me for a chat.
Thank you Alice, it’s good to talk. I am sure that we will do in the future. In the meantime I hope things will get better.  I appreciate you being there.
I’ve been stressing about this, but speaking has helped me sleep and not feel so terrible.
I’ve been stressing about this, but speaking has helped me sleep and not feel so terrible.
This is one of the reasons why we have got Ensos, we recognise the need for speaking out and the link between silence and mental health.
Yes. I see that. Makes sense to me. Simple really. Bye for now.
